column4: hi, if I had 3 processes called tell.exe, update.exe and another one *.exe, using all my cpu,could it be viruses?
I suspect they where running via wine
where are they on your hd?
oh sorry, misunderstood you there. yes, they where on my hd
I'm getting mixed stuff on that
I'd probably just delete the files
but usually when there is a file that I can't open I run it through wine :/
hmmm.. in theory a windows virus could run under wine like that
never heard of it happening. well, it's a first. must be a hostile environment for the poor virus, not even a explorer.exe to restore it after it is gone ;)
working for new ways for windows and linux to co-operate: now you can run windows viruses on linux too!
it could be a big hit!
